RETURN TYPE DEDUCTION (C++14)
=========================================

5 Points to Remember
--------------------

1. Introduced in C++14.
2. Uses `auto` as the return type.
3. Compiler examines all return statements.
4. All return statements must have the same type.
5. Return type is deduced at compile time.


What is Return Type Deduction?
------------------------------
• Introduced in C++14.
• Allows the compiler to automatically deduce a function's return type.
• Use `auto` instead of explicitly specifying the return type.
• Reduces boilerplate and improves readability.

